The defendant Arthur Wilder was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery with Use of Force, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

Defendant Arthur Wilder in court with attorney Debra J Patterson.  Defendant Arthur Wilder in custody.  James W Frisch appeared on behalf of Kimberly D. Schoepp for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms or body armor.  Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  State unable to proceed to sentencing on today's date, due to the numerous read-ins on his misdemeanor case (13CM3914).  Court ordered case continued before Branch 20.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 16, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Debra J Patterson in court, defendant Arthur Wilder not in court, in custody.  Kimberly D Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel requested a plea and sentencing date and to add on the calendar defendant's misdemeanor cases currently set before Branch 47 as part of a global resolution.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for May 27, 2014 at 08:30 am.
Parties request another scheduling date.
TOT to Justice Point: no alcohol or drugs; random testing; no firearms or weapons.
